    "introduction": "The filmmaker began his career as a music editor working alongside his uncle, the renowned editor William M. Anderson. Today, he is himself one of America’s most influential editors, having worked on 16 feature films and over 200 television episodes. Over time, he has also increasingly taken on directing and producing roles, including on Kingdom, American Gods, Hunters and the Golden Globe-winning series The Loudest Voice. Other projects include The Good Lord Bird, the documentary Fightworld and more recently, Ghosts of Beirut and The Georgetown Project.",
